1
00:00:01,080 --> 00:00:02,180
Here.

2
00:00:02,250 --> 00:00:03,500
Use this instead.

3
00:00:05,070 --> 00:00:06,270
What's this?

4
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,200
Wear it...

5
00:00:08,470 --> 00:00:10,470
so you remember who you belong to.

6
00:00:17,730 --> 00:00:19,570
I think about that sometimes.

7
00:00:21,650 --> 00:00:24,010
Honestly, it's been on my
mind more than I expected.

8
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:28,120
Natsume-san.

9
00:00:29,010 --> 00:00:30,510
You startled me.

10
00:00:32,270 --> 00:00:35,360
Those earrings really do look good on you.

11
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:39,300
"Cosmetic Playlover" Season 2
(Episode 5)

12
00:01:42,570 --> 00:01:43,870
Thank you.

13
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:45,750
Thanks.

14
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:49,040
Hoshina's customer service skills

15
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,390
have really stabilized lately.

16
00:01:52,630 --> 00:01:54,230
He's become a reliable part of the team.

17
00:01:54,830 --> 00:01:55,550
That being said,

18
00:01:55,551 --> 00:01:57,540
he's only been here for a month.

19
00:01:57,996 --> 00:01:59,836
We still shouldn't get
too ahead of ourselves.

20
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:00,880
Right.

21
00:02:01,190 --> 00:02:03,190
I want everyone to keep
an eye on him as he grows.

22
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:06,180
We look forward to seeing you again.

23
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:12,870
Welcome.

24
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:14,150
Welcome.

25
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:16,250
Oh, excuse me.

26
00:02:17,083 --> 00:02:18,103
I have an appointment.

27
00:02:18,370 --> 00:02:19,440
We've been expecting you,

28
00:02:19,650 --> 00:02:20,650
Ms. Okada.

29
00:02:21,890 --> 00:02:22,890
I'll leave it to you, then.

30
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,850
Of course, right this way.

31
00:02:25,140 --> 00:02:26,140
Okay.

32
00:02:29,110 --> 00:02:33,660
Ave you had any trouble using the eyeshadow
you bought last time, or any concerns?

33
00:02:34,570 --> 00:02:36,300
Thanks to all your tips,

34
00:02:36,370 --> 00:02:38,040
it's been very easy to use.

35
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,160
I'm glad to hear that.

36
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:42,960
I was thinking of trying
out some blush today too.

37
00:02:43,390 --> 00:02:44,390
Certainly.

38
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:45,973
I'll pick out a few options for you.

39
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,320
Great.

40
00:02:47,410 --> 00:02:48,610
Please wait just a moment.

41
00:02:52,410 --> 00:02:53,570
Hoshina-kun...

42
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:58,380
recently he's quick to grasp what
customers want and handles them very well.

43
00:02:59,260 --> 00:03:00,720
He's good at reading the room, too.

44
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:04,300
He's always been quite observant.

45
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:07,490
Pardon me.

46
00:03:20,630 --> 00:03:22,900
I think this color palette
would suit you perfectly.

47
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:24,340
What do you think?

48
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:26,740
Oh, you're right.

49
00:03:28,460 --> 00:03:32,350
It looks completely different
once you actually put it on.

50
00:03:32,410 --> 00:03:37,140
- Yes, it really complements your skin tone.
- By the way, Hoshina is improving so fast.

51
00:03:38,270 --> 00:03:39,270
I wonder why...

52
00:03:39,970 --> 00:03:41,950
It looks lovely.

53
00:03:42,810 --> 00:03:44,080
Thank you so much.

54
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:45,400
Thanks.

55
00:03:45,790 --> 00:03:47,690
We hope to see you again.

56
00:03:48,020 --> 00:03:50,020
Definitely, I'll be back.

57
00:03:50,540 --> 00:03:52,390
Thank you.

58
00:04:00,537 --> 00:04:01,537
Riku!

59
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:03,150
Oh!

60
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:04,030
Welcome.

61
00:04:04,150 --> 00:04:05,150
You're really here!

62
00:04:05,290 --> 00:04:07,090
We're here to do some
serious shopping today!

63
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:08,760
Thank you, guys.

64
00:04:08,930 --> 00:04:09,930
Welcome.

65
00:04:10,210 --> 00:04:11,200
Are they your friends?

66
00:04:11,230 --> 00:04:12,950
Yes, from university.

67
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:15,170
Oh, are you Mamiya-san by any chance?

68
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:17,180
Yes, that's me.

69
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:19,360
Riku talks about you all the time.

70
00:04:20,340 --> 00:04:23,140
He's been working so
hard on his makeup skills.

71
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,949
He says practicing on us
doesn't make him nervous,

72
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:26,179
so he keeps asking us
to introduce him to friends.

73
00:04:26,180 --> 00:04:27,506
I've lost track of how
many people we've brought.

74
00:04:27,530 --> 00:04:28,580
Hey, stop it already.

75
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:30,700
It's fine. It's good that
you're working hard.

76
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:33,880
Anyway, I pre-ordered a makeup set online.

77
00:04:34,070 --> 00:04:35,940
Yes, thank you.

78
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,700
Right this way, then.

79
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:48,090
Thanks! See you later.

80
00:04:48,115 --> 00:04:49,565
Thanks! Keep it up!

81
00:04:49,626 --> 00:04:51,396
- Bye!
- Bye-bye!

82
00:04:51,970 --> 00:04:53,730
Thank you for coming.

83
00:04:58,820 --> 00:05:01,480
Hoshina, so you've been
practicing on your own time.

84
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:02,980
Um...

85
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:04,670
Yes.

86
00:05:05,730 --> 00:05:08,460
Ever since I started
taking over your clients,

87
00:05:08,810 --> 00:05:10,730
I've been practicing on
weekends and weeknights.

88
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,110
If you'd told me sooner,

89
00:05:12,111 --> 00:05:14,330
I could have adjusted
your training schedule.

90
00:05:14,570 --> 00:05:15,570
No...

91
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:16,900
How do I put this?

92
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:20,309
In the past, no matter
how hard I practiced,

93
00:05:20,310 --> 00:05:21,590
I never saw any results.

94
00:05:22,230 --> 00:05:24,570
I felt so useless.

95
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:27,340
I'd think, "All that work for nothing?"

96
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,760
That's why I wanted to do it secretly...

97
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:31,810
Yes.

98
00:05:32,670 --> 00:05:34,690
Mamiya-san, you've done so much for me.

99
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:37,650
I felt like I needed to work even harder.

100
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:40,960
And when you said I was a reliable asset,

101
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,320
it made me so happy.

102
00:05:45,090 --> 00:05:46,530
What you said...

103
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:48,260
about the meaning of "being trusted."

104
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:50,540
I'm finally starting to understand it.

105
00:05:51,110 --> 00:05:53,030
I'm enjoying work so much more now.

106
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:54,990
I see.

107
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:56,500
- That's great.
- Yes.

108
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:00,260
- I'll get back to work now.
- Okay.

109
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:03,476
Natsume-kun, you're really something.

110
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,476
Hoshina-kun is like a
completely different person.

111
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,580
No, it's all thanks to his own hard work.

112
00:06:07,850 --> 00:06:09,500
And the customers' cooperation.

113
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,580
That's certainly part of it.

114
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:13,980
But I think it's mostly
because the Yurakucho store

115
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:16,100
already has a foundation
for training male BAs.

116
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:19,870
Plus the trust you've
built with your clients.

117
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:23,450
Asking you was definitely the right call.

118
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:25,300
Thank you.

119
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:27,500
I'm the one who should be thanking you.

120
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:29,200
Thank you.

121
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,366
(Sahashi Toma: I have
something to tell you. Call me.)

122
00:06:50,390 --> 00:06:51,390
What is it?

123
00:06:57,310 --> 00:06:58,610
Hello, Natsume-san.

124
00:06:59,190 --> 00:07:00,190
Good work today.

125
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,326
You said you had something
to tell me. What's up?

126
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:03,720
She's getting married.

127
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:05,630
Married? Who?

128
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:07,140
Risako.

129
00:07:07,460 --> 00:07:08,620
The Muse is getting married?!

130
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:14,570
It's still top secret, so keep it down.

131
00:07:15,020 --> 00:07:16,020
Sorry.

132
00:07:17,030 --> 00:07:18,420
But that's wonderful news.

133
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:20,790
Tell her congratulations for me.

134
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:25,759
So, they're planning a bridal shoot

135
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:27,720
for magazines and media announcements.

136
00:07:28,910 --> 00:07:31,780
Romy is contracted for the hair and makeup,

137
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,240
and she specifically requested me.

138
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,360
Again?

139
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,380
That's a huge project.

140
00:07:37,810 --> 00:07:41,050
But... don't you have a lot on your plate
already? Are you sure you can handle it?

141
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,320
Don't overwork yourself.

142
00:07:43,340 --> 00:07:44,340
I know.

143
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:46,790
And here's the main point.

144
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:48,180
Yeah?

145
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,380
Risako...

146
00:07:50,930 --> 00:07:53,330
she requested you join
the project team, too.

147
00:07:54,650 --> 00:07:55,650
What?!

148
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,720
I'm home.

149
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,920
Welcome back.

150
00:07:59,930 --> 00:08:02,720
Hey, what was that call all about?

151
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:03,800
Why me?

152
00:08:04,370 --> 00:08:06,029
During that makeup event,

153
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:08,800
I happened to mention you to Risako.

154
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:10,620
She seems to have remembered.

155
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:12,080
And then...

156
00:08:13,170 --> 00:08:15,400
she saw our poster online

157
00:08:15,860 --> 00:08:17,930
and insisted on having you.

158
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,100
But I...

159
00:08:22,350 --> 00:08:24,809
I've never done anything
like a magazine project.

160
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:27,710
The PR department will be with us,
so it'll be fine.

161
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:29,270
Besides,

162
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,030
as long as I'm with you, Mamiya-san...

163
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,680
I know I can give it my all.

164
00:08:33,190 --> 00:08:34,190
Huh?

165
00:08:38,550 --> 00:08:41,890
Everyone, thank you for coming today.

166
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:45,129
I'm Nakai from the Elly
editorial department.

167
00:08:45,130 --> 00:08:46,130
Nice to meet you.

168
00:08:47,660 --> 00:08:50,940
This is our art director, Mr. Yamamoto.

169
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:52,750
Hello.

170
00:08:53,180 --> 00:08:54,530
I'm Yamamoto.

171
00:08:55,150 --> 00:08:56,970
Nice to meet you all.

172
00:08:57,540 --> 00:08:58,540
And this is...

173
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,999
I'm Risako Yumihara's manager,

174
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,870
Yoshioka from Skylight Agency.

175
00:09:03,890 --> 00:09:05,710
I look forward to working with you.

176
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,500
Nice to meet you.

177
00:09:08,060 --> 00:09:12,610
- This is our stylist, Ms. Yano.
- I'm Yano. Nice to meet you.

178
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,360
Nice to meet you.

179
00:09:16,580 --> 00:09:18,650
Hello, everyone.

180
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:24,490
I'm Asano from HINAKI WEDDING's
planning department. Nice to meet you.

181
00:09:24,580 --> 00:09:26,490
Nice to meet you.

182
00:09:28,950 --> 00:09:31,280
I'm Nishikawa from Crescent Jewelry.

183
00:09:32,070 --> 00:09:33,970
Nice to meet you.

184
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:39,690
I'm Kishimoto from ROMY
FEERIQUE's PR department.

185
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:41,810
I'm Mamiya. Nice to meet you all.

186
00:09:43,530 --> 00:09:46,530
The two of us will be
handling things for now.

187
00:09:46,830 --> 00:09:48,650
Sahashi, who's in charge of the makeup,

188
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,749
is unfortunately fully
booked at the moment.

189
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:52,850
He'll join the team
once the plan is finalized.

190
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:55,560
Is Mamiya-san also from the PR department?

191
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:58,870
Oh, no. I usually work at the counter.

192
00:09:59,490 --> 00:10:00,970
So, you're a BA?

193
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:03,720
Wait, are you the guy from
that men's makeup poster?

194
00:10:04,436 --> 00:10:05,436
Oh.

195
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:06,870
Yes...

196
00:10:08,210 --> 00:10:09,779
Having someone with modeling experience

197
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:11,360
is very reassuring.

198
00:10:11,490 --> 00:10:12,320
Oh...?

199
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,440
Nice to meet you.

200
00:10:13,590 --> 00:10:14,590
Nice to meet you.

201
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,360
Well then, let's get started.

202
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:19,330
Oh, the meeting minutes.

203
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,550
Let me handle that.

204
00:10:22,110 --> 00:10:24,080
It's not like I have
much else to contribute.

205
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,370
I'll leave it to you, then.

206
00:10:26,590 --> 00:10:30,080
Please look at the first
page of the proposal.

207
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:34,150
The theme this time is "The Real Me."

208
00:10:34,180 --> 00:10:36,350
We've prepared five different concepts.

209
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:37,980
The Real Me...

210
00:10:38,830 --> 00:10:42,190
We want to focus on Ms.
Yumihara's more private side.

211
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:45,300
The goal is to show a side of
her no one has seen before.

212
00:10:46,030 --> 00:10:49,479
This draft is based on her
pre-shoot questionnaire, right?

213
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,480
Exactly.

214
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:51,630
It's wonderful.

215
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,256
Every single one is beautiful.

216
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,310
Excuse me.

217
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:56,030
This pink...

218
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:57,169
it's a bit too soft and feminine.

219
00:10:57,170 --> 00:10:59,810
It feels a bit off from
Risako Yumihara's image.

220
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:02,210
I see. We'll adjust that.

221
00:11:02,230 --> 00:11:03,230
Please do.

222
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:05,280
As for the pink...

223
00:11:05,860 --> 00:11:07,580
Reconsider.

224
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:10,579
What about this white one?

225
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:14,309
- That's a classic. It should work.
- But in terms of style...

226
00:11:14,310 --> 00:11:16,609
This season's theme is "Modern x Juicy."

227
00:11:16,610 --> 00:11:19,880
It'd be great if the
styling could highlight that.

228
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:22,100
Modern, no problem.

229
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,340
Feminine style.

230
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:25,670
Needs adjustment.

231
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:28,109
Even a feminine style can work well

232
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:29,376
if we put some effort
into the coordination.

233
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:31,290
But that depends on the direction.

234
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:34,040
Feminine style is okay?

235
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:36,039
When I think of Ms. Yumihara's image,

236
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:38,740
it's more cool and elegant, right?

237
00:11:39,930 --> 00:11:41,130
Cool?

238
00:11:42,060 --> 00:11:43,260
Elegant?

239
00:11:43,420 --> 00:11:44,850
That feels a bit too conservative.

240
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:47,610
I'd like to add a bit of an edge.

241
00:11:48,060 --> 00:11:49,170
Cool.

242
00:11:49,580 --> 00:11:51,920
Elegant is too conservative.

243
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,510
Add some edge.

244
00:11:54,650 --> 00:11:56,866
What if we went bold and gave
the kimono a Western twist?

245
00:11:56,890 --> 00:11:58,090
Exotic style?

246
00:11:58,760 --> 00:11:59,630
Exotic?
I'm sorry.

247
00:12:00,431 --> 00:12:02,600
Our company doesn't really do that style.

248
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,480
Cancel exotic.

249
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:07,050
In that case, the image would be...

250
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,120
By the way,

251
00:12:08,121 --> 00:12:09,880
how do you plan to style the accessories?

252
00:12:10,550 --> 00:12:11,160
Accessories...

253
00:12:11,161 --> 00:12:13,839
We could use more delicate tones
for the accessories...

254
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,389
I don't think that's the right direction.

255
00:12:15,390 --> 00:12:16,160
Excuse me.

256
00:12:16,161 --> 00:12:19,169
Um... we're still hoping for
a bit more of a fresh feel overall.

257
00:12:19,170 --> 00:12:21,680
- Uh... tones... fresh feel...
- So, like brown...

258
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,540
Maybe something like green...

259
00:12:22,541 --> 00:12:24,890
But our new sashes this
season are quite colorful.

260
00:12:24,915 --> 00:12:28,265
It's just... we'd still like to keep
some of the classic elements.

261
00:12:28,382 --> 00:12:36,382
[the clamor of too many
opinions being shared at once]

262
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:40,530
No, no, no...!

263
00:12:40,853 --> 00:12:43,453
This definitely isn't the kind of
work a manager should be doing.

264
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:47,430
Was the meeting really that bad?

265
00:12:47,610 --> 00:12:48,810
It wasn't just bad.

266
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:50,620
I felt completely out of my element.

267
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:52,689
I'm clearly under-experienced.

268
00:12:52,690 --> 00:12:54,980
Why on earth did the Muse pick me?

269
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:56,350
Well...

270
00:12:56,810 --> 00:12:58,940
I called Risako today to ask about that.

271
00:12:59,619 --> 00:13:02,190
Since it's a team made up
of so many different brands,

272
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:05,000
she thought it'd be easier for
me if I had someone I knew there.

273
00:13:05,630 --> 00:13:07,150
What's wrong? Is something the matter?

274
00:13:08,210 --> 00:13:09,210
No.

275
00:13:09,420 --> 00:13:11,119
You shouldn't say "no."

276
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,676
You should say "everything's the matter."

277
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:14,650
If you're the point of contact, Mamiya-san,

278
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:16,950
it definitely makes things easier for me.

279
00:13:17,570 --> 00:13:20,210
And if you really didn't want to
do it, you could've just said no.

280
00:13:20,620 --> 00:13:22,220
No, it's not that...

281
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:25,290
I thought I should try new things.

282
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:27,350
But once I actually got there,

283
00:13:28,230 --> 00:13:29,990
the lineup was so
intense it intimidated me.

284
00:13:31,290 --> 00:13:32,490
It'll be fine.

285
00:13:33,070 --> 00:13:34,800
You're not alone, Mamiya-san.

286
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:36,550
Just think of it as helping me out.

287
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,760
Helping you...

288
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,040
Yeah.

289
00:13:44,630 --> 00:13:45,630
You're right.

290
00:13:46,603 --> 00:13:48,443
There's no point in moping around.

291
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:50,700
Alright.

292
00:13:50,870 --> 00:13:52,070
Since I've taken this on,

293
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:54,910
I'll make sure everything is
perfect before I hand it over to you.

294
00:13:55,110 --> 00:13:56,310
Leave it to me.

295
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:57,780
Okay~

296
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:15,900
I have a business trip to Osaka next week.

297
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,480
Again?

298
00:14:20,590 --> 00:14:21,790
That's rough.

299
00:14:22,030 --> 00:14:23,030
I'm used to it.

300
00:14:25,790 --> 00:14:31,070
You don't need to tell him to
"take it easy" or "get some rest."

301
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:35,010
When he's worn out, he'll come
to me for comfort on his own.

302
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:37,790
But if...

303
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:40,400
this becomes a
long-distance relationship...

304
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,240
What's wrong?

305
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,270
Let's just go to sleep.

306
00:14:59,110 --> 00:15:00,110
Okay.

307
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:14,190
Mamiya-san,
I'm so sorry.

308
00:15:15,161 --> 00:15:17,500
I'm tied up with another
project and can't make it today.

309
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:18,980
Huh?

310
00:15:19,540 --> 00:15:20,540
Mamiya-san,

311
00:15:20,850 --> 00:15:22,150
I'm counting on you.

312
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:27,410
I'm on my own for todays meeting?!

313
00:15:31,196 --> 00:15:33,875
Ms. Yumihara made an appearance today.

314
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:36,510
Thanks to you, we've
had an excellent meeting.

315
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:38,000
Thank you very much.

316
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,410
Thank you very much.

317
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,620
Thank you all.

318
00:15:40,820 --> 00:15:42,476
I feel like this is going
to be a wonderful project.

319
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:44,530
I'm looking forward to the shoot.

320
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:46,570
Regarding the next meeting,

321
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:49,090
I'll notify you by email. I look
forward to working with you.

322
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:50,550
Nice to meet you.

323
00:15:51,940 --> 00:15:53,450
Good work today.

324
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:57,220
- I'll go get the car. Wait for me here.
- Okay.

325
00:15:57,710 --> 00:16:00,020
- Good work.
- Good work.

326
00:16:03,490 --> 00:16:04,880
Mamiya-san.

327
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:06,880
Yes, how can I help you?

328
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:09,480
About this shoot,

329
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:12,410
do you think we could use this eyeshadow?

330
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:14,440
Excuse me.

331
00:16:14,441 --> 00:16:16,370
Could I see the product number?

332
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:18,790
- Sure.
- Thank you.

333
00:16:22,030 --> 00:16:24,940
ROMY FEERIQUE, Shimmering Orange...

334
00:16:25,180 --> 00:16:26,180
Pardon me.

335
00:16:33,110 --> 00:16:34,340
I'm very sorry,

336
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,530
but this item has been discontinued.

337
00:16:40,190 --> 00:16:41,906
If you're looking for
something currently available,

338
00:16:41,930 --> 00:16:45,100
shade #5 from the ROMY FEERIQUE
"Fruit" series is the closest match.

339
00:16:46,170 --> 00:16:48,570
If you want a dewy, pearlescent look,
you could go with #3...

340
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:49,820
Oh.

341
00:16:50,177 --> 00:16:51,177
Oops.

342
00:16:51,850 --> 00:16:54,010
I accidentally slipped into
my customer service voice.

343
00:16:54,810 --> 00:16:56,070
That's amazing.

344
00:16:56,620 --> 00:16:57,716
Knowing which items are discontinued

345
00:16:57,740 --> 00:16:58,940
and suggesting alternatives...

346
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:00,660
You were able to answer right away.

347
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:02,880
Do you have all of them memorized?

348
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:05,370
Yes, for the most part.

349
00:17:06,513 --> 00:17:08,293
As expected of an active BA.

350
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:10,780
I'm so glad I suggested
your name, Mamiya-san.

351
00:17:11,310 --> 00:17:14,450
No, it's just one of the few
ways I can actually be of help.

352
00:17:15,990 --> 00:17:16,990
Here you go.

353
00:17:17,390 --> 00:17:18,510
Thank you.

354
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:31,040
I'll finish up quickly

355
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:32,650
and go home with him.

356
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:37,510
This is for the location shoot.

357
00:17:41,150 --> 00:17:43,350
Ms. Yumihara

358
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,060
wants to use shade #5
from the Fruit series...

359
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:56,440
That eyeshadow.

360
00:17:56,970 --> 00:17:58,970
It looks like she's been
using it for a long time.

361
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:02,880
And it's a really old product number.

362
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:11,780
So, these are the final five concepts.

363
00:18:13,970 --> 00:18:15,040
Oh, this one is...

364
00:18:15,570 --> 00:18:18,130
A classic bridal makeup style.

365
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:21,530
But we also want to bring out a cool edge
to match Ms. Yumihara's image.

366
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,280
And this one has more of an Oriental feel.

367
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:26,130
Can I start on the makeup designs?

368
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:27,800
Yes.

369
00:18:28,410 --> 00:18:31,560
It'd be great if you could have them ready
by next weekend's meeting.

370
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,400
Okay.

371
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:45,010
Thanks.

372
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:48,410
With the image so clear,
it'll be easy to design.

373
00:18:51,550 --> 00:18:52,550
I see.

374
00:18:52,890 --> 00:18:53,890
That's good.

375
00:18:54,890 --> 00:18:56,650
Will you be there for
the shoot, Mamiya-san?

376
00:18:56,970 --> 00:18:58,170
Yeah, officially.

377
00:18:58,430 --> 00:18:59,459
If you're going to be there,

378
00:18:59,460 --> 00:19:00,830
I'll have to show off a bit.

379
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,880
You should work hard even if I'm not there.

380
00:19:03,270 --> 00:19:04,670
I know, I know.

381
00:19:10,830 --> 00:19:12,030
I'm so relieved.

382
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:14,510
I was worried at first,

383
00:19:15,060 --> 00:19:17,140
but I've successfully handed
everything off to Toma.

384
00:19:17,340 --> 00:19:18,469
It looks like things will
go smoothly from here.

385
00:19:18,470 --> 00:19:19,610
Please wait a moment.

386
00:19:22,460 --> 00:19:23,460
Manager.

387
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:25,880
- A call from the PR department.
- Okay.

388
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:30,230
Hello, this is Mamiya.

389
00:19:31,150 --> 00:19:32,150
Yes.

390
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:34,370
I'm glad we've finally reached a milestone.

391
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:37,200
Wait...

392
00:19:41,770 --> 00:19:43,070
Starting from scratch?!

393
00:19:45,940 --> 00:19:47,450
I see...

394
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:50,750
I understand...

395
00:19:55,070 --> 00:19:56,400
Hey, Mamiya.

396
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:58,020
What's with that look on your face?

397
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:00,680
Heh.

398
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:06,580
Redo everything?

399
00:20:06,860 --> 00:20:08,419
I'm so sorry.

400
00:20:08,420 --> 00:20:10,090
Especially when you're already so busy...

401
00:20:10,540 --> 00:20:12,600
This isn't something you
should be apologizing for.

402
00:20:13,390 --> 00:20:14,580
I understand the situation.

403
00:20:15,150 --> 00:20:18,310
It would be a huge help if you
could get the new plan to me ASAP.

404
00:20:18,420 --> 00:20:19,420
Okay.

405
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:21,120
I have to go to a meeting now.

406
00:20:21,350 --> 00:20:22,950
I'll send you the schedule later.

407
00:20:23,140 --> 00:20:24,880
- Please do.
- Yeah.

408
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:29,060
In this project,

409
00:20:29,380 --> 00:20:32,060
the most important element is the dress.

410
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:34,160
The role of the makeup is

411
00:20:34,710 --> 00:20:36,750
to harmonize with the project's worldview

412
00:20:37,460 --> 00:20:38,660
and enhance its beauty.

413
00:20:41,410 --> 00:20:42,510
Therefore,

414
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,859
we've decided to start with the dress

415
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:46,720
and re-evaluate the entire styling.

416
00:20:47,090 --> 00:20:50,500
We didn't expect the same dress
to be used in a TV drama first.

417
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:53,036
If she wears it after that,

418
00:20:53,060 --> 00:20:55,160
it'll put her at a disadvantage.

419
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:59,640
The concept and location haven't changed.

420
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,750
Time is limited,

421
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:02,980
but let's do our best.

422
00:21:04,420 --> 00:21:05,420
Mr. Yamamoto...

423
00:21:05,810 --> 00:21:07,920
Until the styling is finalized,

424
00:21:08,450 --> 00:21:10,080
Toma can't even start his work.

425
00:21:11,260 --> 00:21:13,306
I want to hand things off
to him as soon as possible.

426
00:21:13,330 --> 00:21:14,330
Ms. Asano,

427
00:21:14,580 --> 00:21:16,040
are there any suitable dresses?

428
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:21,589
Um... the person in
charge is searching urgently.

429
00:21:21,590 --> 00:21:24,170
I'm very sorry...

430
00:21:24,970 --> 00:21:27,630
- Please keep looking.
- I can't exactly rush them here.

431
00:21:28,970 --> 00:21:30,430
This is so frustrating.

432
00:21:32,490 --> 00:21:33,330
Yes.

433
00:21:33,331 --> 00:21:34,850
It's shade #5 from the Fruit series.

434
00:21:35,740 --> 00:21:36,740
Oh, you have it in stock?

435
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:38,739
I'm actually in the neighborhood.

436
00:21:38,740 --> 00:21:40,020
Can I stop by?

437
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:43,290
Thank you so much.

438
00:21:43,870 --> 00:21:45,670
Alright, I'll see you soon.

439
00:21:45,710 --> 00:21:46,770
Talk to you later.

440
00:21:48,530 --> 00:21:49,530
Whew.

441
00:21:50,390 --> 00:21:52,070
As expected of the Ginza store.

442
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:54,030
I'm glad they had it.

443
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:56,730
Oh! Mamiya-kun.

444
00:21:57,330 --> 00:21:58,570
Nanjo-san.

445
00:21:58,590 --> 00:21:59,470
What's up?

446
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,720
What brings you to our store?

447
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,889
I'm here for Risako Yumihara's project.

448
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:05,130
I wanted to check the stock
for a limited edition color.

449
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:07,640
You're as serious as ever.

450
00:22:08,970 --> 00:22:13,150
Sahashi-kun is helping out at the Shibuya
store. Want me to take a look for you?

451
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:17,700
Here, take this.

452
00:22:18,290 --> 00:22:20,090
Thank you.

453
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,320
No problem.

454
00:22:26,870 --> 00:22:27,870
Alright.

455
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:31,090
And this too.

456
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,369
Sorry, thank you.

457
00:22:33,370 --> 00:22:34,370
Here you go.

458
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:36,280
Thanks.

459
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:38,880
But seriously,

460
00:22:38,905 --> 00:22:40,534
Sahashi-kun is really pushing himself.

461
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,770
Taking on a project
during such a busy time,

462
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:47,340
plus all the assignments Emma's giving him.

463
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:48,960
Assignments?
Yeah.

464
00:22:49,621 --> 00:22:50,869
After the store closes,

465
00:22:50,870 --> 00:22:53,370
he gets the staff or
the manager to help him

466
00:22:54,010 --> 00:22:55,389
film videos to send to Emma.

467
00:22:55,390 --> 00:22:56,870
He's really dedicated to his studies.

468
00:22:57,370 --> 00:22:59,760
I saw the reply, but I can't accept this.

469
00:22:59,970 --> 00:23:01,850
Doesn't this stray from the Romy style?

470
00:23:05,130 --> 00:23:07,210
If we do this, the
impression will be too weak.

471
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,680
Wow...

472
00:23:08,810 --> 00:23:10,600
He's actually arguing with Emma.

473
00:23:11,010 --> 00:23:13,430
He's working harder than anyone expected.

474
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:15,820
He's starting to look
more like you, Mamiya-kun.

475
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:17,140
No.

476
00:23:17,510 --> 00:23:19,250
That's just who he is.

477
00:23:21,090 --> 00:23:22,990
He never wavers.

478
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:34,080
Sorry about that.

479
00:23:37,170 --> 00:23:38,920
If Sahashi-kun goes to Paris,

480
00:23:39,250 --> 00:23:40,530
won't you guys be long-distance?

481
00:23:42,870 --> 00:23:45,310
Since I'm the one who
mentioned him to Emma,

482
00:23:45,950 --> 00:23:47,460
I feel a bit responsible.

483
00:23:49,630 --> 00:23:50,630
Don't be.

484
00:23:51,370 --> 00:23:53,530
We were just given the option.

485
00:23:54,890 --> 00:23:56,630
He's the one who has to make the decision.

486
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,240
I see.

487
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:07,800
Exactly.

488
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:11,330
Toma is the one who will
decide for himself if he'll go to Paris.

489
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:14,000
And that's exactly why

490
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:15,980
I want to support him.

491
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:18,260
What do you think of the result?

492
00:24:19,850 --> 00:24:20,850
It looks really good.

493
00:24:21,490 --> 00:24:22,670
Thank you.

494
00:24:22,990 --> 00:24:23,990
For his sake,

495
00:24:25,210 --> 00:24:27,030
I'm going to see this
wedding project through

496
00:24:27,810 --> 00:24:29,970
and hand it off to Toma properly.

497
00:24:32,700 --> 00:24:34,349
(Next Episode)
Being happy, being apart...

498
00:24:34,350 --> 00:24:36,420
Don't say things like that.

499
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:37,810
What do you like about him?

500
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:38,840
Everything.

501
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,410
As a Romy BA,

502
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:42,370
I'll give him my heartfelt blessings.
